      "factorType": "Numerical code verification",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Order-of-accuracy tests and method-of-manufactured-solutions (MMS) verification must confirm correct numerical implementation for all governing equations used in the hemolysis model.",
      "rationale": "MMS verification was performed for the Navier-Stokes solver but not for the scalar hemolysis transport equation. Achieved level 3 is below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Systematic mesh refinement study with Richardson extrapolation or equivalent must demonstrate discretization error below 5% for hemolysis index QoI.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study was completed; Richardson extrapolation yields approximately 8% discretization error on peak hemolysis index, exceeding the 5% threshold. Achieved level 3 is below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation must match VAD operating envelope (flow rate, rotational speed, fluid properties) to within specified tolerances.",
      "rationale": "Bench experiments were conducted at three of the five target operating points. Two high-speed operating points lack matching experimental data. Achieved level 3 is below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison metric (e.g., E-metric or normalized RMS error) between model predictions and experimental hemolysis index must be computed with uncertainty bounds.",
      "rationale": "Quantitative comparison was performed at three operating points with E-metric computed; uncertainty bounds are available but the two unvalidated operating points prevent a complete comparison. Achieved level 3 is below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The modeled QoI (normalized index of hemolysis, NIH) must be directly traceable to the clinical acceptability criterion for VAD patient safety.",
      "rationale": "NIH is the primary QoI and is directly linked to the clinical threshold. However, sub-lethal red blood cell damage metrics used in the power-law model have not been independently validated for the specific pump geometry. Achieved level 4 is below required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 4,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must be performed on the same pump geometry, fluid, and operating regime as the COU, or differences must be formally characterized via similarity analysis.",
      "rationale": "Validation used the FDA generic pump geometry which closely matches the COU pump; however, the blood analog fluid viscosity differs from clinical blood properties by approximately 12%. No formal similarity bridging analysis was performed. Achieved level 4 is below required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Numerical solver error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Iterative convergence, round-off error, and solver residuals must be documented and shown to be negligible relative to discretization error for all simulation runs.",
      "rationale": "Solver residual histories were not systematically archived for all five operating-point simulations. Iterative convergence criteria were set but not verified post-hoc. This factor is flagged as an epistemic gap at MRL 5; achieved level 2 is well below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Use error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Evidence of independent review of simulation setup, boundary condition specification, and post-processing procedures must be documented to detect operator errors.",
      "rationale": "No independent review of simulation setup was performed. A single analyst configured all boundary conditions and post-processing scripts without peer verification. This represents an uncharacterized epistemic gap. Achieved level 2 is below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The power-law hemolysis model form must be justified through comparison with alternative constitutive models and sensitivity analysis on model-form assumptions.",
      "rationale": "The Giersiepen-Wurzinger power-law model was selected without comparison to alternative hemolysis models (e.g., strain-based or energy dissipation models). Model-form uncertainty is unquantified. This is a critical epistemic gap at MRL 5. Achieved level 2 is far below required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters (fluid properties, power-law coefficients, turbulence model constants) must have documented sources, uncertainty bounds, and sensitivity rankings.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ was performed on geometric and flow boundary condition inputs, but the power-law hemolysis coefficients (C, alpha, beta) were held fixed at literature values without uncertainty characterization. Achieved level 3 is below required level 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test samples",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 4,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental samples used in validation testing must be characterized for material properties, geometric tolerances, and batch-to-batch variability to support uncertainty quantification.",
      "rationale": "The FDA generic pump test specimens used in bench validation were not individually characterized for geometric tolerances. Batch variability in the blood analog fluid is undocumented. Achieved level 2 is below required level 4."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Equivalency of input parameters",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "A formal parameter equivalency analysis must demonstrate that input parameters used in the validation scenario are representative of or formally mapped to COU input parameter space.",
      "rationale": "No formal equivalency analysis was conducted between validation scenario input parameters and the COU operating envelope. The two unvalidated high-speed operating points fall outside the range of any validation data. Achieved level 2 is far below required level 5."
